name: Kaiju Zanga - Red Version
description: Here it is at last, KAIJU ZANGA! Mark Nagata's new desert Kaiju for the heavyweight division! Check out the size of the Dunny next to Zanga!! Only 1 available - first 2 sold in the first few hours of going on display. Artist: Mark Nagata Sculptor: Yuichi Yamashita Manufacturer: Max Toy Co. Platform: Zanga Size: 12 inch

name: Alien Argus (Ghost Of The Dead Abyss) - Skinner x Mark Nagata
description:
Toy Art Gallery has teamed up with Skinner to release the “Ghosts of the Dead Abyss” Alien Argus. 
Designed by Mark Nagata, this version of the Argus is decorated with metallic blue, purple and red on a base of black vinyl.

Artist: Skinner x Mark Nagata 
Sculptor: Masami Yamada 
Manufacturer: Max Toy Co. 
Platform: Alien Argus 
Size: 10 inch

name: King Negora - Konatsu x Max Toy
description:
King Negora was designed by cat-loving Japanese artist, Konatsu, and cat-crazy Japanese-American artist, Mark Nagata. 
The 9.5-inch vinyl figure was sculpted by Makino-san of TTToys and cast in white vinyl by Master Shimizu-san. 
This is the first painted version of King Negora, and it comes with Oh Nezumi Rat.

Artist: Konatsu x Mark Nagata
Sculptor: Yoshihiko Makino
Manufacturer: Max Toy Co.
Platform: King Negora
Size: 10 inch

name: Custom Patty Power - Arbito x Super 7
description:
Here's my lucky pull from the Super 7 Lucky Bag 2012 - A one off custom Patty Power by Arbito.
Pink sofubi with purple sprays, handpainted with silver and purple paint.
On the back is painted "Patty Power" in silver paint (really clean!).
Signed on the bottom of the foot "Arbito".
A rare custom by Arbito, havent seen any others from the 2012 Lucky Bag.

Artist: Arbito
Manufacturer: Super 7
Platform: Patty Power
Series: Monster Family
Size: 4 inch
